# shellcheck shell=bash
# Phorj toolchain / gate-oracle configuration — EDIT HERE.
#
# Single source of truth for the machine-specific tool paths the quality gate needs.
# Sourced by scripts/git-hooks/pre-push, and by any manual gate run:
#     source scripts/toolchain.env && cargo test --workspace
#
# PHORJ_PHP — the PHP byte-identity oracle. MUST be the 8.5 transpile-floor build, NOT the
# 8.6-dev `php` on PATH (that build is too permissive to gate against — see CLAUDE.md). When the
# stack reloads and the phpbrew php version changes, update the version in the path below and
# nothing else needs to move.
#
# An explicit `PHORJ_PHP=… ` in the environment still wins over this default (the `:-` keeps the
# override working), so CI or a one-off run can point elsewhere without editing this file.
PHORJ_PHP="${PHORJ_PHP:-/stack/tools/phpbrew/php/php-8.5.8/bin/php}"

# Rust toolchain is pinned separately by rust-toolchain.toml (rustup reads it automatically);
# it is intentionally NOT duplicated here to avoid a second source of truth.
